m now until December, again,\noperating dollars, the capital dollars that are there. The budget will come out\non the 7th. ","index":"00443","speaker":"Scott Fielding"},{"html":"����� This will�interim appropriation is\nthe funding source for the government interim�until the appropriation act gets\npassed later on in the year. ","index":"00444","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Chairperson:</b> Okay, if there\nno further questions, is the committee ready for the question? ","index":"00445","speaker":""},{"html":"Shall the resolution\npass? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00446","speaker":""},{"html":"����� So now we'll go to the fourth\nresolution pertaining to part D, Capital Investments By Other Reporting\nEntities for Interim Supply reads as follows: ","index":"00447","speaker":""},{"html":"����� RESOLVED that there be granted to\nHer Majesty, for the fiscal year ending March 31st, 2022, a sum not exceeding\n$2,005,097,000 being 90 per cent of total amount set out in 2020 Estimates,\nincluding Supplementary Estimates, for the purpose set out in part D, Capital\nInvestments by the Other Reporting Entities, of those Estimates. ","index":"00448","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Does the minister have any opening\ncomments? No. Does the official opposition Finance critic have any opening\ncomments? ","index":"00449","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>����� </b>The floor is open for\nquestions. Any questions? No questions? ","index":"00450","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Shall the resolution pass? <i>[Agreed]</i>","index":"00451","speaker":""},{"html":"����� That concludes business before the\ncommittee. ","index":"00452","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Committee\nrise. ","index":"00453","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Call\nin the Speaker.","index":"00454","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><span style=\"text-transform:uppercase\">IN\nSESSION</span></b>","index":"00455","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable member for Arthur-Virden.","index":"00456","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Doyl